name: $code
desc: Returns: A code that is used to identify the property. The code is used internally (in CodeSystem.concept.property.code) and also externally, such as in property filters.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: A code that is used to identify the property. The code is used internally (in CodeSystem.concept.property.code) and also externally, such as in property filters.

name: $uri
desc: Returns: Reference to the formal meaning of the property. One possible source of meaning is the [Concept Properties](codesystem-concept-properties.html) code system.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Reference to the formal meaning of the property. One possible source of meaning is the [Concept Properties](codesystem-concept-properties.html) code system.

name: $description
desc: Returns: A description of the property- why it is defined, and how its value might be used.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: A description of the property- why it is defined, and how its value might be used.

name: $::type
desc: Returns: The type of the property value. Properties of type "code" contain a code defined by the code system (e.g. a reference to anotherr defined concept).
